Ideally the param annotation wouldn't be needed here, but TS has trouble with inference for some reason. Reduced test case:

```tsx
type Props<Suggestion, Section> = {
    sections: Section[];
    getSectionSuggestions: (section: Section) => Suggestion[];
    getSuggestionValue: (suggestion: Suggestion) => string;
};

declare class Autosuggest<Suggestion, Section> extends React.Component<
    Props<Suggestion, Section>
> {}

// Example usage

type Section = { title: string; suggestions: string[] };
declare const sections: Section[];

<Autosuggest
    sections={sections}
    getSectionSuggestions={section => section.suggestions}
    getSuggestionValue={suggestion => suggestion} // error
    // Workaround:
    // getSuggestionValue={(suggestion: string) => suggestion}
/>;
```

